Executive director stated that the operation has re-created serious incident report form and included a section for documentation as to the requirements needed for a serious incident report would need. Executive director stated that the same form will be used for incidents that do not constitute a serious incident report and are more behavioral incidents. A copy of the previous/current Serious incident form was obtained. Executive Director also stated that staff were reminded about reporting and documentation through the meeting on 9/15/2023. Staff are expected to complete Serious Incident form and reporting within 24 hours. Staff interviewed stated the expectation the operation has implemented is to have any serious incident reports/non-serious incident report are to be completed as soon as possible before their shift is over. The report is to be filled out by the person with firsthand knowledge and the report must be detailed. "
